      {"text": "Determine whether the perspective is correct yes/no. Projection: Strict Orthographic Isometric Projection. What this means: Complete absence of realistic perspective. All parallel lines on the object remain parallel in the image; they never converge at a single point on the horizon. Command: Do NOT use perspective view or camera with 2 vanishing points. Camera height: High-angle shot. What this means: The camera looks down on the object from above, at an angle of approximately 30-35 degrees to the horizontal plane. Visual marker: We should see a significant portion of the tree canopy. Command: Imitate the view as if we were looking at an architectural model or an object in a strategy game. DO NOT shoot from eye level. Rotation angle: Classic game angle. What this means: The object is rotated so that its conditional front is facing the viewer. Visual marker: Vertical lines trunk remain perfectly vertical. No distortion: What this means: All proportions are preserved. The object in the background does not become smaller. Vertical parts do not tilt."},
      {
        "inline_data": {
          "mime_type": "image/jpeg",
